The article announces several nominations and appointments made by the United States government. Some of the notable appointments include James H. Anderson as Assistant Secretary of Defense, Rubydee Calvert as a Member of the Board of Directors of the Corporation for Public Broadcasting, Bonnie Glick as Deputy Administrator of the United States Agency for International Development, Jennifer L. Homendy as a Member of the National Transportation Safety Board, Heidi R. King as Administrator of the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration, and John P. Pallasch as Assistant Secretary of Labor. The article also mentions various appointments for United States District Judges, United States Marshals, and United States Attorneys in different districts across the country.